<img width="1657" alt="screen shot 2019-02-23 at 10 32 27 pm" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3223098/53295952-04c5e180-37bb-11e9-8402-b8d59c94446e.png">

Great job. I think my previous listed concerns doesn't exist based on the test. I attached my screenshoot of the latest graph view. So I put up some comments in the code which some of them may not apply now based on my test.

> 1. There is already a serialized representation of DAGs so DB serialization should probably go through that even though that might be a bit more work.

@aoen What do you mean by this point?

I don't see how security factors in to this PR/AIP at all  - it doesn't change anything fundamental about how Airflow currently works, and is no better or worse for multi-tenancy than Variables, connections, or workers speaking directly to the DB anyway.
